The paper deals with the problem of information spreading in dynamic networks, which is a topic in distributed computing (cs.DC). The focus is on gossip algorithms, which involve communication between nodes, making it relevant to networked systems (cs.NI) and social networks (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the role of adversaries in modifying the network, which falls under the category of security and privacy (cs.SY). Finally, the paper presents lower and upper bounds on the performance of different algorithms, which involves mathematical analysis and complexity theory (cs.IT).
